22
00:01:02,799 --> 00:01:05,075
The purpose of this presentation is to know

23
00:01:05,075 --> 00:01:08,566
if the use of a motility measure is relevant and useful

24
00:01:08,566 --> 00:01:10,089
for a better understanding

25
00:01:10,089 --> 00:01:12,682
of the issue of large job-related mobilities.

26
00:01:12,927 --> 00:01:14,897
This presentation is based on a survey conducted

27
00:01:14,897 --> 00:01:16,243
in four countries:

28
00:01:16,243 --> 00:01:19,396
Germany, Spain, France and Switzerland.

29
00:01:19,396 --> 00:01:20,826
They are panel data

30
00:01:20,826 --> 00:01:23,951
that is to say that the same people were surveyed for the first time in 2007,

31
00:01:23,951 --> 00:01:25,951
then again in 2011.

32
00:01:25,951 --> 00:01:29,075
Qualitative interviews were also carried out in France,

33
00:01:29,075 --> 00:01:31,192
with a large mobile population.

34
00:01:31,916 --> 00:01:34,412
French and Swiss parts of the second survey wave

35
00:01:34,412 --> 00:01:36,761
were funded by the mobile lives forum.

36
