we sought to characterize the access, skills and projects

45
00:02:00,055 --> 00:02:01,916
in connection with the great mobility.

46
00:02:01,916 --> 00:02:04,080
We start here by access.

47
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:07,692
Contextual said access were characterized in our research

48
00:02:07,692 --> 00:02:11,588
by the proximity of a highway, a regional train line,

49
00:02:11,588 --> 00:02:14,416
a large railway and airport.

50
00:02:14,416 --> 00:02:16,557
Thus, 9 out of 10

51
00:02:16,557 --> 00:02:20,177
have a highway or a regional train line less than 20 minutes.

52
00:02:20,177 --> 00:02:23,783
60% of people on average have an airport less than 45 minutes away

53
00:02:23,783 --> 00:02:27,005
and a large railway less than 20 minutes away.

54
00:02:27,005 --> 00:02:31,317
The presence of railway infrastructure is even more important since we know that

55
00:02:31,317 --> 00:02:34,147
more than the distances are large,

56
00:02:34,147 --> 00:02:36,052
more the use of the train increases

57
00:02:36,052 --> 00:02:38,208
mainly because the transport time

58
00:02:38,208 --> 00:02:40,641
can be upgraded more easily than by car,

59
00:02:40,641 --> 00:02:43,400
for example by working or resting.

60
00:02:43,666 --> 00:02:46,107
Beyond these contextual access,

61
00:02:46,107 --> 00:02:48,906
it is necessary to discuss personal access

62
00:02:48,906 --> 00:02:52,198
starting with the car or other motorized modes

63
00:02:52,198 --> 00:02:53,946
like the two-wheeled motors type,

64
