as does Martin, always by my side,

90
00:04:14,730 --> 00:04:18,426
Another point of useful skills for mobility.

91
00:04:19,230 --> 00:04:23,510
The projects on mobility vary widely among individuals.

92
00:04:23,841 --> 00:04:27,911
To consider them, we questioned the disposition of these people

93
00:04:27,911 --> 00:04:31,341
to move to another region, overseas,

94
00:04:31,341 --> 00:04:34,165
to commute more than a two-hour round trip,

95
00:04:34,165 --> 00:04:36,112
to make frequent trips to their work,

96
00:04:36,112 --> 00:04:39,281
or to take a pied-a-terre and doing a round-trip

97
00:04:39,281 --> 00:04:42,408
every week between here and the main housing.

98
00:04:42,892 --> 00:04:47,144
37% of people on average say they would commute

99
00:04:47,144 --> 00:04:50,170
against 18% for moving abroad.

100
00:04:50,170 --> 00:04:52,020
Based on all of these elements,

101
00:04:52,020 --> 00:04:53,770
we have been able, through

102
00:04:53,770 --> 00:04:55,241
statistical analysis

103
00:04:55,241 --> 00:04:58,904
of factor analysis type and hierarchical classification,

104
00:04:58,904 --> 00:05:02,992
to construct a typology of motility in connection with the mobility.

105
00:05:03,611 --> 00:05:07,221
We got six groups we offer now

106
00:05:07,221 --> 00:05:10,110
to describe in pairs of opposites.

107
00:05:10,110 --> 00:05:12,187
The first of these pairs of opposites returns

108
00:05:12,187 --> 00:05:16,946
to an ordinal reading of motility, that is to say to have more or less of it.

109
00:05:16,946 --> 00:05:19,203
Low mobile on one side,

110
00:05:19,203 --> 00:05:23,440
are people who combine low access, low skills,

111
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:26,699
with no project for mobility.

112
00:05:27,175 --> 00:05:30,067
Conversely, highly mobile people have good access,

113
00:05:30,067 --> 00:05:32,258
their skills are more developed

114
00:05:32,258 --> 00:05:34,179
and they say they are ready to move

115
00:05:34,179 --> 00:05:37,315
and ready for most forms of mobility.

116
00:05:38,172 --> 00:05:42,572
Note that people with higher levels of education and income

117
00:05:42,572 --> 00:05:47,097
are found in greater proportion in the highly mobile group.

118
00:05:47,353 --> 00:05:52,817
The second pair of opposition concerns reversible and non-reversible.

119
00:05:52,817 --> 00:05:56,160
It allows to highlight the opposition in projects

120
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:58,224
between people who are willing to relocate

121
00:05:58,224 --> 00:06:01,731
but not wishing to commute, and those who think the opposite,

122
00:06:01,731 --> 00:06:04,025
that is to say they do not want to move,

123
00:06:04,025 --> 00:06:07,132
but are ready for intensive commuting.

124
00:06:07,132 --> 00:06:10,527
This returns to questions of anchoring at residence.

125
00:06:10,527 --> 00:06:13,416
This anchoring can be linked with being the owner,

126
00:06:13,416 --> 00:06:17,864
but also a residential location close to relatives or friends,

127
00:06:17,864 --> 00:06:19,957
or even an attachment to places

128
00:06:19,957 --> 00:06:22,132
in which routines were implemented.

129
00:06:22,132 --> 00:06:25,293
This opposition is also that of a vision of what

130
00:06:25,293 --> 00:06:26,693
the quality of life for people

131
00:06:26,693 --> 00:06:28,295
who do not wish to be forced

132
00:06:28,295 --> 00:06:31,832
to spend several hours daily in transportation.

133
00:06:32,264 --> 00:06:36,400
We can clearly see that there is no group more mobile than the other.

134
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:42,088
Reversible nor non-reversible are more gifted than the other.

135
00:06:42,557 --> 00:06:46,032
The approach of mobility allows especially here to highlight

136
00:06:46,032 --> 00:06:48,530
lifestyles that are different.

137
00:06:48,530 --> 00:06:51,657
To simplify the reading of the last couple of opposition

138
00:06:51,657 --> 00:06:54,429
we propose to combine the access and skills

139
00:06:54,429 --> 00:06:57,784
in what might be called power, being great mobile,

140
00:06:57,784 --> 00:07:01,452
while projects concerned the will to be great mobile.

141
00:07:01,452 --> 00:07:07,232
Thus, those reluctant to move far can move, but do not want to.

142
00:07:07,232 --> 00:07:09,767
